NODE_3_length_118620_cov_260.980168	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	84723	87389	.	+	0	ID=MGA_330;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;;locus_tag=LOCUS_03270;note=WP_005809460.1 FtsX-like permease family protein (Desulfitobacterium) [pid:23.6%25%2C q_cov:53.7%25%2C s_cov:61.1%25%2C Eval:4.0e-26%2C partial hit],Domain:cl27391:FtsX FtsX-like permease family. Members of this protein family are found%2C so far%2C only in three species of Acidobacteria%2C namely Acidobacteria bacterium Ellin345%2C Acidobacterium capsulatum ATCC 51196%2C and Solibacter usitatus Ellin6076%2C where they form large paralogous families. Each protein contains two copies of a domain called the efflux ABC transporter permease protein (pfam02687). However%2C unlike other members of that family (including LolC%2C FtsX%2C and MacB)%2C genes for these proteins are essentially never found fused or adjacent to ABC transporter ATP-binding protein (pfam00005) genes. We name this family ADOP%2C for Acidobacterial Duplicated Orphan Permease%2C to reflect the restricted lineage%2C internal duplication%2C lack of associated ATP-binding cassette proteins%2C and permease homology. The function is unknown. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:269-401%2C Eval:9.8e-09%2C score:55.4%2C N-term missing],MGA_330
