NODE_4_length_118353_cov_188.869635	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	113088	113744	.	-	0	ID=MGA_453;product=16S rRNA (guanine(966)-N(2))-methyltransferase RsmD;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_013582362.1;translation=MRIIGGEWRGRKIEEPRGRDVTRPTTDRVREACASMVMSAFDFDLDEVRVLDAFGGSGALGIEMLSRGARSLTTFEIDRNAARLITKNNESLCRDRARWRVVTGDMLASASRGRVPGGPFDLVLLDPPYAFGAEPVEELLQDLAQQGLLASGAYVLFEHAAADAGAHPAGFETVREKRYGITSVDLLRWVGDDDGEGDSAGTDADNNDATTFQEDAHE;locus_tag=LOCUS_04500;gene=rsmD;EC_number=2.1.1.171;note=WP_013582362.1 16S rRNA (guanine(966)-N(2))-methyltransferase RsmD (Bifidobacterium longum) [pid:37.1%25%2C q_cov:88.5%25%2C s_cov:94.6%25%2C Eval:3.1e-23],Domain:cl17173:AdoMet_MTases N/A. SAMBD is the domain at the N-terminus of proteins arginine methyltransferase 10 proteins. Protein arginine methyltransferases catalyze the transfer of methyl groups from S-adenosylmethionine - SAM - to arginine residues in target proteins thereby releasing S-adensoylhomocystein - SAH - as a product. Post-translational modification of arginine plays important roles in the eukaryotic cell such as signal transduction.This SAM-binding domain forms part of the catalytic core of the enzyme. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:1-188%2C Eval:1.0e-51%2C score:162.8],MGA_453
