NODE_8_length_79374_cov_211.735576	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	11900	12379	.	+	0	ID=MGA_711;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;translation=MAKSIQHNVAYVACGSGCASAGGDARCSEGCIGCGACVAACPHGAIALVDGIARVDRSKCTGCGLCGMACPQRVIAFVPGYQNILVRCNNTDKGAIARKICDTSCIGCGMCAKKCPAGAIRIEDNCAHIDGVDCLSCGMCAVVCPHGAIHDRTGIAAGV;locus_tag=LOCUS_07060;note=WP_008761242.1 Fe-S cluster domain-containing protein (Bacteroides) [pid:45.1%25%2C q_cov:86.2%25%2C s_cov:48.5%25%2C Eval:2.1e-31%2C partial hit],TIGR:TIGR02700%3B flavo_MJ0208: archaeoflavoprotein%2C MJ0208 family [Name:TIGR02700%2C Eval:6.0e-19%2C score:66.2%2C bias:29.7],Domain:cl27605:NIR_SIR Nitrite and sulphite reductase 4Fe-4S domain. Dissimilatory sulfite reductase catalyzes the six-electron reduction of sulfite to sulfide%2C as the terminal reaction in dissimilatory sulfate reduction. It remains unclear however%2C whether trithionate and thiosulfate serve as intermediate compounds to sulfide%2C or as end products of sulfite reduction. Sulfite reductase is a multisubunit enzyme composed of dimers of either alpha/beta or alpha/beta/gamma subunits%2C each containing a siroheme and iron sulfur cluster prosthetic center. Found in sulfate-reducing bacteria%2C these genes are commonly located in an unidirectional gene cluster. This model describes the alpha subunit of sulfite reductase. [Central intermediary metabolism%2C Sulfur metabolism] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:28-74%2C Eval:3.4e-11%2C score:57.0%2C C-term missing],Domain:cl28181:AAA ATPases associated with a variety of cellular activities. Members of this family are ATP-binding cassette (ABC) proteins by homology%2C but belong to energy coupling factor (ECF) transport systems. The architecture in general is two ATPase subunits (or a double-length fusion protein)%2C a T component%2C and a substrate capture (S) component that is highly variable%2C and may be interchangeable in genomes with only one T component. This model identifies many but not examples of the downstream member of the pair of ECF ATPases in Firmicutes and Mollicutes. [Transport and binding proteins%2C Unknown substrate] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:52-132%2C Eval:4.7e-10%2C score:53.8%2C C-term missing],MGA_711
