NODE_9_length_78711_cov_286.472785	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	33976	34218	.	-	0	ID=MGA_800;product=FeoA family protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_005811001.1;translation=MSCGPQMPAMPLSMVKAGETVRVSRVKGNEDMKHHLKDLGFVEGSEIHVVSSSGANIIVTVLGARFGIDSKVAMHIMTVG;locus_tag=LOCUS_07930;note=WP_005811001.1 FeoA family protein (Desulfitobacterium hafniense) [pid:42.7%25%2C q_cov:93.8%25%2C s_cov:78.1%25%2C Eval:1.3e-10],Domain:cl00838:FeoA FeoA domain. This domain also occurs at the C-terminus in related proteins. The transporter Feo is composed of three proteins: FeoA a small%2C soluble SH3-domain protein probably located in the cytosol%3B FeoB%2C a large protein with a cytosolic N-terminal G-protein domain and a C-terminal integral inner-membrane domain containing two 'Gate' motifs which likely functions as the Fe2+ permease%3B and FeoC%2C a small protein apparently functioning as an [Fe-S]-dependent transcriptional repressor. Feo allows the bacterial cell to acquire iron from its environment. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:10-77%2C Eval:6.0e-12%2C score:52.6],MGA_800
NODE_9_length_78711_cov_286.472785	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	34407	34655	.	-	0	ID=MGA_801;product=HPr family phosphocarrier protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_007051543.1;translation=MVEFTKTIKDPLGLHARPVALLYDIIAKHRSDVSVSIGDRHTDGRDVMGLMALYGECGEDIIFRVSGVDEASCVTSIRNLSL;locus_tag=LOCUS_07940;note=WP_007051543.1 HPr family phosphocarrier protein (Bifidobacterium longum) [pid:36.8%25%2C q_cov:82.9%25%2C s_cov:79.1%25%2C Eval:1.4e-07],Domain:cl00206:PTS-HPr_like N/A. The HPr family are bacterial proteins (or domains of proteins) which function in phosphoryl transfer system (PTS) systems. They include energy-coupling components which catalyze sugar uptake via a group translocation mechanism. The functions of most of these proteins are not known%2C but they presumably function in PTS-related regulatory capacities. All seed members are stand-alone HPr proteins%2C although the model also recognizes HPr domains of PTS fusion proteins. This family includes the related NPr protein. [Signal transduction%2C PTS] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:1-80%2C Eval:5.7e-15%2C score:60.7],MGA_801
