NODE_12_length_49651_cov_254.638621	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	42226	46599	.	-	0	ID=MGA_867;product=2-hydroxyacyl-CoA dehydratase;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_002382252.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_08600;note=WP_002382252.1 2-hydroxyacyl-CoA dehydratase (Enterococcus) [pid:37.2%25%2C q_cov:98.6%25%2C s_cov:97.2%25%2C Eval:2.4e-244],COG:COG1924:YjiL Activator of 2-hydroxyglutaryl-CoA dehydratase (HSP70-class ATPase domain) [Category:I%2C Aligned:141-575%2C Eval:1.1e-112%2C score:358.6],Domain:cl21559:HGD-D 2-hydroxyglutaryl-CoA dehydratase%2C D-component. Members of this family include various bacterial hypothetical proteins%2C as well as CoA enzyme activases. The exact function of this domain has not%2C as yet%2C been defined. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:675-1016%2C Eval:4.1e-80%2C score:265.5],Domain:cl21559:HGD-D 2-hydroxyglutaryl-CoA dehydratase%2C D-component. Members of this family include various bacterial hypothetical proteins%2C as well as CoA enzyme activases. The exact function of this domain has not%2C as yet%2C been defined. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:1052-1449%2C Eval:7.1e-68%2C score:232.7],Domain:cl17037:NBD_sugar-kinase_HSP70_actin Nucleotide-Binding Domain of the sugar kinase/HSP70/actin superfamily. FtsA is essential for bacterial cell division%2C and co-localizes to the septal ring with FtsZ. It has been suggested that the interaction of FtsA-FtsZ has arisen through coevolution in different bacterial strains. The FtsA protein contains two structurally related actin-like ATPase domains which are also structurally related to the ATPase domains of HSP70 (see PF00012). FtsA has a SHS2 domain PF02491 inserted in to the RnaseH fold PF02491. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:22-240%2C Eval:1.4e-41%2C score:155.6%2C N-term missing],MGA_867
