NODE_20_length_34040_cov_260.170951	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	24126	26087	.	+	0	ID=MGA_1073;product=Stk1 family PASTA domain-containing Ser/Thr kinase;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_010965035.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_10600;gene=pknB;note=WP_010965035.1 Stk1 family PASTA domain-containing Ser/Thr kinase (Clostridium) [pid:33.8%25%2C q_cov:94.3%25%2C s_cov:93.0%25%2C Eval:6.2e-90],COG:COG0515:SPS1 Serine/threonine protein kinase  [Category:T%2C Aligned:10-270%2C Eval:3.3e-57%2C score:195.7%2C C-term missing],Domain:cl02768:PASTA N/A. This domain is found at the C termini of several Penicillin-binding proteins and bacterial serine/threonine kinases. It binds the beta-lactam stem%2C which implicates it in sensing D-alanyl-D-alanine - the PBP transpeptidase substrate. It is a small globular fold consisting of 3 beta-sheets and an alpha-helix. The name PASTA is derived from PBP and Serine/Threonine kinase Associated domain. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:365-620%2C Eval:1.2e-37%2C score:139.5],MGA_1073
NODE_20_length_34040_cov_260.170951	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	26652	27959	.	+	0	ID=MGA_1074;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;;locus_tag=LOCUS_10610;note=WP_011475608.1 site-specific integrase (Ligilactobacillus salivarius) [pid:24.8%25%2C q_cov:57.5%25%2C s_cov:58.8%25%2C Eval:1.2e-14%2C partial hit],TIGR:TIGR02224%3B recomb_XerC: tyrosine recombinase XerC [Name:TIGR02224%2C Eval:5.7e-18%2C score:63.2%2C bias:0.0],Domain:cl28330:XerC Integrase [Replication%2C recombination and repair%2C Mobilome: prophages%2C transposons]. The phage integrase family describes a number of recombinases with tyrosine active sites that transiently bind covalently to DNA. Many are associated with mobile DNA elements%2C including phage%2C transposons%2C and phase variation loci. This model represents XerD%2C one of two closely related chromosomal proteins along with XerC (TIGR02224). XerC and XerD are site-specific recombinases which help resolve chromosome dimers to monomers for cell division after DNA replication. In species with a large chromosome and with homologs of XerD on other replicons%2C the chomosomal copy was preferred for building this model. This model does not detect all XerD%2C as some apparent XerD examples score below the trusted and noise cutoff scores. XerC and XerD interact with cell division protein FtsK. [DNA metabolism%2C DNA replication%2C recombination%2C and repair] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:67-413%2C Eval:1.2e-10%2C score:59.1],MGA_1074
